The paper deals with the problem of dense reconstruction of objects in natural sequences of images, which is a classic problem in computer vision. The proposed method incorporates a 3D object prior obtained through deep learning, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of deep learning also suggests that the paper could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The problem of object reconstruction also involves geometric reasoning, which could place the paper in the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the use of bundle adjustment methods suggests that the paper could also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
